narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I gained an understanding of many coding languages and how to program (C, Python, SQL, HTML, Javascript, CSS)
Thorough introduction to programming. Learned basic C, Python, SQL, JavaScript, HTML, CSS, but most importantly how to learn more languages.

I have learned so much about coding and the different languages. I have learned how to implement the language in various scenarios and how to problem solve using different techniques. Debugging my code was a great skill to learn and it can be used with any language in the future.
I gained knowledge of several programming languages. I also learned how to think more logically.
This was the first computer science class Ive ever taken and it taught me how to think about programming and gave a very broad based introduction to computer science.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The course is taught in a very engaging way, both in the recorded lectures and in person at section.

I really liked how we did labs and walkthroughs during the class times! Sometimes I wish the TAs would steer us in the right direction because there were times were I was so stuck I wasnt able to do anything. But I understand why they just threw us straight into it.
The flipped classroom was really good for me. Also my teachers were super helpful.
I thought doing labs and practice with programming was very helpful. You will most likely have to spend a lot of time in office hours doing the problem sets.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, it is a excellent course to start your CS journey (whether you major in it or not)
Absolutely - an amazing introduction to computer science with very supportive staff!

I think this course provides a great baseline on anything coding and teaches one how to learn other languages and allows us to become self sufficient in a way. I would recommend this class to almost everyone on campus.
Yes!
Yes. If you want a comprehensive intro to CS and are willing to put in the work, this course is very rewarding.

narratives.question_text: How will you use the knowledge and skills you learned in this course in your future endeavors?
comments: All the languages we learned will be extremely helpful going forward. I am excited to see where I may use these new skills next!

This way of thinking can be used in almost every aspect of life and will be useful to solving problems I reach in the real world. I think my coding career will continue past this class and I will be very grateful to have learned how to use some of these languages and find bugs in my code and learn new languages if need be.
I think the coding skills I learned in this class will be applicable to many future endeavors.
